<Prose
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The practical terms for working with Styled by Susanne: booking, written quotes, 48-hour rescheduling, clothing budgets, affiliate links, and governing law."
  eyebrow="Policies"
  intro="The practical ground rules for working together, written to be read, not skimmed past."
  dateline="Draft, last updated July 18, 2026"
>
  <h2>Booking and quotes</h2>
  <p>
    Every engagement starts with a complimentary 30-minute style conversation.
    Services are booked only after that conversation and a written quote, so
    you always know the exact scope and price before anything is committed.
    Published price ranges on this site describe typical scope; your written
    quote is the number that counts.
  </p>

  <h2>The style conversation carries no obligation</h2>
  <p>
    The conversation is free, and it obligates you to exactly nothing. If the
    recommendation doesn&rsquo;t feel right (or the timing isn&rsquo;t right),
    you simply don&rsquo;t book, and we part as friends.
  </p>

  <h2>Cancellations and rescheduling</h2>
  <p>
    Life happens; closets wait. You can cancel or reschedule a session at no
    charge with at least 48 hours&rsquo; notice. Inside 48 hours, a
    rescheduling or cancellation fee may apply; the specific terms for your
    engagement are stated in your written quote.
  </p>

  <h2>Your clothing budget</h2>
  <p>
    Your clothing budget is separate from my service fees. You set it, you
    control it, and purchases are made in your own accounts unless we agree
    otherwise in writing. My fee never depends on how much you spend on
    clothes.
  </p>

  <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
  <p>
    Some links on this site are affiliate links, which may earn me a
    commission at no extra cost to you. How that works (and the programs
    involved) is explained in the
    <a href="/policies/affiliate-disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Styling guidance, not guarantees</h2>
  <p>
    Everything on this site and in our sessions is personal-styling guidance
    based on my professional judgment and experience. I&rsquo;ll bring my full
    attention and honest advice to your closet, but style is personal and
    results vary; no specific outcome is promised or guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h2>Site content</h2>
  <p>
    The content on this site (words, photographs, and guides) is
    &copy; Styled by Susanne. Please don&rsquo;t republish it without
    permission. (Sharing a link, on the other hand, is always welcome.)
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Illinois, where the
    studio is based.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
  <p>
    This is a working draft, pending formal legal review before launch. If the
    terms change, the date at the top of this page changes with them.
  </p>

  <p>
    Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
  </p>
</Prose>
